Reasoning: This paper discusses the linguistic style of tweets and uses geographic data to analyze the correlation between readability and education. This falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) as well as social and information networks (cs.SI), social computing (cs.SOC), and machine learning (cs.LG) due to the use of data analysis techniques. Additionally, the use of census data and geographic information systems (GIS) suggests a potential fit for the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
